mutant: m029_plan_continuation_cursor_off_by_one
target: internal/manifest/plan.go
failure-mode: |
  The truncated-page continuation cursor is advanced one seq too far
  (lastUnitMaxSeq + 1 instead of lastUnitMaxSeq). PlannedThroughSeq is an
  EXCLUSIVE lower bound for the next page (afterSeq = PlannedThroughSeq), so
  reporting last+1 makes the next page start at afterSeq = last+1, which drops
  every block whose MaxSeq == last+1 (the very next unit) — a silently skipped
  page boundary. Under the paginated client loop the union of pages is missing
  the row(s) straddling each truncation seam.
expected-detection: |
  Killed by TestPartB_MultiPageBackfillCutover / TestPartB_MidSegmentTruncation
  (#182, partb tier): the union of paginated pages no longer equals ground
  truth (a boundary row is skipped), so emittedSeqs diverges from the expected
  contiguous run. Not reachable from TestOracle_DefaultLifecycle, whose default
  MaxEntries never truncates a plan.
expected-tier: partb
tiers: partb

diff --git a/internal/manifest/plan.go b/internal/manifest/plan.go
--- a/internal/manifest/plan.go
+++ b/internal/manifest/plan.go
@@ -234,7 +234,7 @@ func (m *Manifest) PlanBackfill(req PlanBackfillRequest) (PlanBackfillResult, er
 	}

 	if truncated {
-		result.PlannedThroughSeq = lastUnitMaxSeq
+		result.PlannedThroughSeq = lastUnitMaxSeq + 1
 	}

 	return result, nil
